@@TJvAlignListbox
<GROUP TJvAlignListbox>
Summary
  List box that can align items.
Description
  TJvAlignListbox is a TCustomListBox descendant that has an Alignment property to set the alignment
  of the items.
Note
  When you declare an OnDrawItem event, the Alignment property has no use, as it's completely
  bypassed by the event handler.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAlignListbox.AboutJVCL
  <INCLUDE JVCL.Main.AboutJVCL.dtx>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAlignListbox.Alignment
Summary
  Indicates how the text should be aligned.
Description
  Alignment indicates how the text should be aligned in the list box. Alignment uses the VCL's
  <EXTLINK borland://TAlignment>TAlignment</EXTLINK> type to indicate the alignment type.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAlignListbox.DrawItem
Summary
  Draws a list box item.
Description
  DrawItem draws a list box item aligned according to the Alignment property. However, if the
  OnDrawItem event is assigned, the event will be called instead (which is in essence the same as
  a TListBox with the Style property set to lbOwnerDraw).
See Also
  Alignment
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAlignedEdit.SetAlignment
Summary
  Changes the edit's alignment.
Description
  SetAlignment set a new alignment for the edit control. After changing it the window is recreated.

  SetAlignment is the set method for the Alignment property.
See Also
  Alignment
